## Data Format

All datasets should be preprocessed to `data/processed/` as `.mat` files with this structure:

```matlab
data.time           % [N x 1] seconds
data.voltage        % [N x 1] volts
data.current        % [N x 1] amps (positive = charge)
data.temperature    % [N x 1] celsius (or kelvin)
data.soc            % [N x 1] fraction [0,1]  (if available)
data.cycle          % scalar cycle number (for aging studies)
data.cell_id        % string identifier
data.chemistry      % 'NMC', 'LFP', 'LCO', etc.
```

---

## Parameter Fitting from Data

Use `data/` files to fit SPM parameters:

### 1. Capacity from CC discharge
```matlab
Q = trapz(t, abs(I)) / 3600;   % Ah
```

### 2. OCV–SOC from slow discharge (C/20)
```matlab
% Discharge at C/20 → voltage profile ≈ OCV
OCV_curve = [soc_vector, voltage_vector];
```

### 3. Internal resistance from pulse test
```matlab
% ΔV at step current onset / ΔI
R_int = (V_before_pulse - V_immediately_after) / delta_I;
```

### 4. Diffusion coefficient from GITT
```matlab
% Galvanostatic Intermittent Titration Technique
Ds = 4/pi * (I_pulse * Vm / (z_A * F * A))^2 * (dE_dSOC / dE_dsqrt_t)^2;
```

